Item.Review:
Pros: I have used this same exact model for a few years now, I always by this one when the previous one breaks, usually it's because I end up chewing through the wires, and I keep dropping them. but even with all that 1 lasts me about a year +/- 2 months. but they're cheap($$) but professional feel
Cons: when you drop them the earpiece pops out, but it pops right back in so idk if that's really a con. the cable are a bit too long for my taste, but comes with a roller to roll up the extra wires. idk if you need the long wire it's not a con.
if you want to save money, buy this. if you treat your headphones like poop then this would be good for you(like me)
